    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "> 1. Is calling another matplotlib backend from another backend (=ipython inline backend) possible? (Putting aside IPython and zmq, it is a pure Python question.)\n\nNo. Once you select a backend, you are stuck with it for the remaining lifetime of the Python process.\n\n> 1. It means calling backend function from kernel Python instance, not from frontend Python instance, right? Meaning that you cannot use it via ssh unless you have X port forwarded and having some functions to treat DISPLAY environment. Am I correct?\n\nYes - a GUI backend is tied to the display on which it is launched, so you have to do X forwarding, etc. to forward windows.  The inline backend is the only _reasonable_ way to forward images across the network with matplotlib.\n\n> 1. Do you think these functions fit with IPython?\n\nI don't understand this question.\n"
  },
