    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "What I meant by calling a matplotlib backend from another backend was something this:\n\n``` python\n# mixedbackend.py\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    import matplotlib\n    matplotlib.use('module://mixedbackend')\n\n    from pylab import show, plot, randn\n    plot(randn(100), randn(100), 'o', alpha=0.5)\n    show()\n\n    import mixedbackend\n    mixedbackend.usewhat = 'wx'\n    from pylab import show, plot, randn\n    plot(randn(100), randn(100), 'o', alpha=0.5)\n    show()\n\n\nfrom matplotlib.backends import backend_qt4agg, backend_wx\n\nusewhat = 'qt4agg'\n\n\ndef new_figure_manager(*args, **kwds):\n    if usewhat == 'qt4agg':\n        return backend_qt4agg.new_figure_manager(*args, **kwds)\n    else:\n        return backend_wx.new_figure_manager(*args, **kwds)\n\n\ndef draw_if_interactive(*args, **kwds):\n    if usewhat == 'qt4agg':\n        return backend_qt4agg.draw_if_interactive(*args, **kwds)\n    else:\n        return backend_wx.draw_if_interactive(*args, **kwds)\n\n\ndef show(*args, **kwds):\n    if usewhat == 'qt4agg':\n        return backend_qt4agg.show(*args, **kwds)\n    else:\n        return backend_wx.show(*args, **kwds)\n```\n\nYou will see first Qt4Agg window and then Wx window.  I guess it is a very bad hack and not mean to do exactly the same as above.  What I wanted to show is that in principle, if you write a proper FigureManager etc., I think you can have two backends _internally_ and switching them depending on context.  What do you think?\n\nBut it will be complicated job to do and I was wondering if this complexity is worth having in IPython.  You will also need to implement X forwarding to use this complex backend over the wire.\n\nSo, maybe popup image is the better solution?\n"
  },
